ADO EKITI – The Secretary of the former and serving National ex-officio members of the People’s Democratic Party(PDP), Hon. Hellen Taiwo-Adebakin has facilitated with the chieftain of the party and former member of the House of Representatives, Hon Ladi Adebutu on the occasion of his 60th birthday. Adebakin, in her birthday message to the PDP icon in the Southwest described  Adebutu as one of the pillars of the party in the zone. She acknowledged Adebutu’s contributions to the unity and progress of the party in the SouthWest, particularly, Ogun State where he hails from. Birthday Anniversary: Adebakin Rejoices With Oyinlola New Year: Adebakin Congratulates Nigerians, Says Help On The Way Unlike other former PDP leaders who dumped the party at the trying times, Adebakin said Adetutu had stayed put spending his time and resources for the repositioning of the party in the state. The PDP chieftain, however, urged Adebutu not to relent In his efforts at ensuring the victory of the party in the coming elections in Ogun State. ” While wishing you a happy birthday,I also acknowledged your immense efforts at ensuring that our party returns to power in Ogun State. I wish you many more of the day in prosperity and good health. I say happy birthday to political leader and mentor.” Adebakin said.